{
  "texts": [
    "Constraining κ * from light curve data has proceeded largely by applying the fitting method of Kochanek (2004).",
    "Studies using this approach have adopted a different strategy to calculating κ, γ from a macromodel and having κ * as a free parameter.",
    "Their mass model consists of a combination of a NFW halo and a concentric de Vaucouleurs component of the mass in stars, obtained by fitting the light of the lensing galaxy and a constant mass-to-light ratio (see also Lehar et al. 2000).",
    "The total mass being conserved, a single free parameter, f ML, describes the combination of the two components, from purely stars (f ML = 1) to just a NFW halo (f ML = 0).",
    "Varying this parameter leads to different κ, γ, κ * combinations, not just κ * (and also a varying mass-to-light ratio across the lensing galaxy)."
  ]
}